6.3 Data Minimisation and Handling Rules
Collection minimisation
Only collect data required for the specific compliance purpose. No speculative collection. Each field must have a documented legal basis and purpose before addition to any form.
Biometric data isolation
Biometric raw data (facial images, scans) stored in a physically separate storage layer with separate encryption key. Not accessible to application layer — only to identity verification service via one-way API.
PII in logs — prohibition
No PII (name, DOB, ID number, address, email) may appear in application logs, error messages, or system monitoring outputs. Log references use tokenised customer IDs only.
Pseudonymisation in analytics
All analytics and reporting outputs use pseudonymised or anonymised data. Real customer PII never appears in dashboards, exports, or reports accessible to analyst-level roles.
Data masking in non-production
Development, staging, and testing environments must use synthetic data or masked production data. Real PII is never copied to non-production environments.
Cross-border transfer controls
Transfer of personal data outside the originating jurisdiction is restricted. UAE data to non-adequacy countries requires explicit consent or Standard Contractual Clauses equivalent. KSA PDPL requires data localisation for sensitive data — no transfer without SDAIA approval. ADGM DPR 2021 requires transfer mechanisms equivalent to GDPR Chapter V.
 
