SECTION 08
Admin Configuration Layer
M-15 is the platform's no-code/low-code control centre. It determines how every other module behaves for a given tenant, customer type, product, and jurisdiction combination. All configuration is versioned, audit-logged, and resolvable at runtime.
 
8.1 Configuration Hierarchy
Configuration resolves from most specific to least specific. The most specific applicable configuration wins.
 
Level 1 — Platform Defaults
Baseline configuration applied to all tenants. Set by platform operator. Cannot be overridden below compliance baseline. Examples: minimum retention periods, mandatory screening lists, UBO threshold floor.
Level 2 — Tenant Configuration
Tenant-level customisation. Applies to all products and customer types for that tenant unless overridden at lower level. Examples: brand settings, default language, primary jurisdiction rules.
Level 3 — Product Configuration
Per-product rules. A tenant may operate multiple products (e.g. corporate account, personal account, investment product) with different onboarding requirements. Examples: document requirements, CDD level, approval path.
Level 4 — Customer Type Configuration
Rules applied per entity type (individual / corporate / trust / fund / HNWI). Can override product-level where entity-specific rules apply. Examples: UBO depth, EDD triggers, risk weight adjustments.
Level 5 — Jurisdiction Override
Jurisdiction-specific rules applied when a customer is from or operating in a specific country. Applied on top of product and customer type config. Examples: FATF high-risk country EDD requirement, KSA-specific document type, UAE QFZP treatment.
 
