9.2 How Vertical Adaptation Works Without Rebuilding
Step 1 — Template selection
Tenant admin selects the closest matching industry template from the M-15 library. This loads a pre-validated baseline configuration.
Step 2 — Field customisation
Tenant adds, removes, or reorders fields relevant to their product using the form builder. Compliance-mandatory fields cannot be removed.
Step 3 — Document requirements
Tenant configures acceptable document types, optional documents, and conditional document logic (e.g. "if activity is trading, require commercial licence").
Step 4 — Risk weight calibration
Tenant adjusts risk scoring weights to reflect their product risk profile within the permitted bands. MLRO approval required to activate.
Step 5 — Integration hookup
Tenant configures API keys for their chosen IDV provider, screening provider, and notification service via M-15 integration settings.
Step 6 — Jurisdiction overlay
If the tenant operates in multiple jurisdictions, jurisdiction-specific rule overlays are applied on top of the base template. Each overlay addresses country-specific document types, data fields, screening lists, and approval requirements.
Step 7 — Test and activate
Workflow is tested in sandbox mode against representative customer profiles. MLRO or compliance officer reviews and activates.
 
